<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08316</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT GRANTING RETIREMENT BENEFITS TO ALL BARANGAY OFFICIALS WHO HAVE RENDERED AT LEAST 3 (THREE) TERMS OF CONTINUOUS SERVICE AND PROVIDING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Grants lump sum retirement benefits to elected barangay officials equivalent to one and a half (1 ½ ) month of his/her last honorium for every year of service which shall be taken form the Barangay Retirement Fund. 

Prohibits barangay officials who were convicted of a crime or have pending criminal or administrative cases filed against them from availing the said retirement benefits. 
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Barangay Officials Retirement Benefits Act.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CALIXTO-RUBIANO, EMI G.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-10-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Robes (000 2018-10-10)</td><td>2. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-11-21)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LOCAL GOVERNMENT ON 2018-10-03</td></tr></table>